  "description": "Lebanese-Canadian executive who served as President/COO of MindGeek alongside CEO Feras Antoon through the company's peak years, holding (with Antoon) 99.7% of MindGeek S.à.r.l. per Luxembourg's beneficial-ownership registry. The *Fleites v. MindGeek* complaint alleges this share was held on behalf of the controlling beneficial owner Bergmair as compensation for running day-to-day operations.",
